tissueExpression.summary: Cytoplasmic and nuclear expression in essentially all cell types except stroma cells and cells in glomeruli.
Most normal tissues displayed moderate to strong cytoplasmic and/or nuclear positivity. Renal glomeruli, ovarian and endoemtrial stroma cells were negative.
Moderate to strong cytoplasmic and/or nuclear positivity was observed in most malignancies. Several lung, skin and renal cancers were weakly stained or negative.

tissueExpression.summary: Most normal tissues showed moderate to strong nuclear and cytoplasmic positivity. Squamous epithelia, trophoblastic cells, liver, endometrial stroma and muscle myocytes were weakly stained or negative.

Most malignant cells showed weak to moderate nuclear and cytoplasmic positivity. Malignant glioma, ovarian, endometrial, stomach and pancreatic cancers displayed cases with strong positivity. Malignant melanoma, urothelial and renal cancers were negative in several cases.
